news.title: China Evergrande sticks to restructuring plan target of before end-July
news.para: Reeling under more than $300 billion in liabilities, the firm's offshore debt is deemed to be in default after missing payment obligations late last year.

news.title: Mastercard inks 20-year lease for 4.23 lakh sq ft office space in Brookfield's Pune property
news.para: The deal is an indication of rising numbers of leasing through pre-commitments as corporates are locking in large office spaces across the country in the backdrop of reviving expansion plans. Large technology, consulting, and financial services firms like Google, Amazon, Qualcomm and Wells Fargo have pre-committed large office space across major cities in the last few quarters.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against Nirmal Lifestyle Kalyan
news.para: Kolkata-based Srei Equipment Finance Ltd had approached the Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) after Nirmal Lifestyle Kalyan, an affiliate of Mumbai-based Nirmal Lifestyle Ltd, defaulted on its dues worth around Rs 84 crore.

news.title: Over 120 dangerous buildings in Ghaziabad, but no evacuation yet
news.para: ​Meanwhile, the list of those buildings has kept growing, with the GMC identifying 122 of them this year, including multi-storey towers and government buildings.

news.title: Seven arrested after builder's staff assault Noida society residents
news.para: The clash took place on Sunday at the Sunshine Helios premises in Sector 78, under Sector 113 police station limits, allegedly over conflict between the Apartment Owners Association (AoA) of the society and the builder's personal-hired security men, the officials said.

news.title: Jaipur development body seals six-story building over construction violations
news.para: Between January 1 and May 30, the JDA had sealed 112 buildings. The seals of nine buildings were opened after the owners followed the directions of the civic bodies.

news.title: Jharkhand: Real estate sector suffers Rs 30,000 crore loss in six months, says trade body
news.para: Builders and traders on Monday said the halt in supply of sand has not only led to losses in real estate but also adversely affected the livelihood of people who are dependent on allied sectors like material supply and construction labour.

news.title: Nagpur Residents march to NMC over lack of basic amenities, property rights
news.para: The residents of Slum Rehabilitation Scheme at Nari, Uppalwadi, pressed for various demands including road, streetlights, regular water, grocery shop and primary health centre.

news.title: Gurugram: Monsoon at doorstep, but rainwater harvesting pits defunct in upscale colonies
news.para: The team observed that the RWH pits had stagnant water and waste accumulated causing further pollution to the groundwater. “These pits require intensive cleaning and maintenance for proper functioning,” a team member said.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body issues notices to 308 more highrises over fire NOCs
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) issued notices warning that any more delays will invite disconnection of water and electricity connections according to the Gujarat Fire Prevention and Life Safety Measures (Amendment) Act, 2021.

news.title: Need-based changes report to be discussed at Chandigarh housing board meet
news.para: Recently, CHB’s need-based changes panel recommended certain relaxations. With the committee constituted to study requests to allow more need-based changes in residential units, CHB allottees are likely to get some relief.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: Drafted in 2018, Lift Act yet to get nod
news.para: But four years on, there’s been no movement. Multiple states in India, including Maharashtra, have such laws to govern the functioning of lifts.

news.title: Trilegal leases 40,000 sq ft in Delhi, companies focus on return to work
news.para: A third of the quarter’s leasing (Jan-March) comprised of large transactions (above 100,000 sf) across micro-markets in Gurugram and Noida with some occupiers also locking hard options for future expansion plans, according to consultants.

news.title: About 2,970 unclaimed Amrapali flats to be auctioned?
news.para: About 2,970 buyers, who had booked their flats and likely paid at least a portion of the total sale amount, have not filed their claims as mandated by the rules despite several extensions.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP will hire private agency for status check of Mahira Homes
news.para: DTCP is poised to take charge of the project in Sector 68 after the builder’s licence was cancelled last month for allegedly submitting forged documents and bank guarantees.
